Key Match Events: Dawid Malan and Chris Woakes scored fifty-plus runs
Wickets fell rapidly for Netherlands in the latter stages of their innings
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes is player of the match and is more pleased to get a win
Woakes praises England’s recent record and acknowledges the team’s desperation to perform
Buttler is happy with the win but acknowledges the team’s struggles and the importance of the World Cup
Scott Edwards notes his team didn’t start well and gives credit to England for batting well
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch was a good one, back of a length with tennis-ball bounce
England’s net run-rate improved to -0.88, putting them above Bangladesh and Sri Lanka
Netherlands lost their last five wickets for 16 runs
